body:
When Verilating a module that contains wires with a colon in their names, the VCD produced by verilator is rejected by GTKWave. 

Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)
```module test_mod(b, clk, a);
    input clk;
    input a;
    output b;
   
    wire \test_sig_with_colon:3419 ;

endmodule
```
I wasn't aware that colons were allowed in verilog identifiers, however yosys produces verilog with them in it and verilator accepts it as valid. 

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
I am running verilator built from commit 9f37cef1bb.

What OS and distribution are you using?
Ubuntu 20.04

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

Yes please. I have written a patch that fixes this locally, but I'm not entirely sure if this should be fixed in verilator or GTKWave, or whether this is the right way to fix it
